      "content": "Minimum wage hikes, especially in areas with lower cost of living, can be a double-edged sword for small businesses. On one hand, they can lead to increased consumer spending power, which can benefit local businesses. On the other hand, they can also strain small businesses' profit margins and potentially lead to job cuts or reduced hours for employees. It's crucial to balance the economic benefits with the potential challenges faced by small businesses.",
